Former Ekiti State Governor Peter Ayodele Fayose on Friday led three governors of the All Progressives Congress (APC) to meet Rivers State governor Nyesom Wike. Fayose, a member of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) arrived at Wike’s residence with governor Kayode Fayemi of Ekiti State, Babajide Sanwo-Olu of Lagos State and Rotimi Akeredolu of Ondo State. A closed-door meeting is ongoing between the APC governors and Wike. Details later. 